node.text: Every life experience sits within the landscape of your body. When faced with any kind of heightened stress, moving is key to your resiliency. Moving to music while learning how to manage your own personal energy is also your built-in restoration process. A brand new artist, @carlykingbadabing who is sure to grow our souls through her music for lifetimes to come, is helping me move today with her breakout hit, Mountains. To help you manage your stress and stay patient, I am sharing all 12 minutes of the latest arms sequences from my Online Studio today on IGTV. Please move with it as many times as you need 🤍 #counteveryvote

node.text:
Healthy living is more than eating right and meeting fitness goals. It’s also important for me to have the most knowledge possible to plan for my future health. That’s why I teamed up with @Invitae, they make it so easy to incorporate genetic health screening into your lifestyle, so you can get info on any inherited cardio or cancer risks, and can be even better in-tune with your body. All you do is initiate an order online, provide a saliva sample, and mail it back for processing.
And, it’s #BreastCancerAwarenessMonth and women’s health is especially top of mind. In addition to annual screenings and mammograms, a genetic test can help you better understand your breast cancer risk, even without family history. #MyInvitae #InvitaePartner

node.text:
Meet the strong, inspiring women in our community who I'll be moving for on October 28th—Tracy, Susan, Alicia, Debi, and Aimee • @tracyfitfamilylife @susan.rothman @awt.tam @fit.debi @boymomstam

In 2015, we partnered with the Breast Cancer Research Foundation (@bcrfcure) to support BCRF’s life-saving programs through Move to Cure – a program that’s galvanizing the fitness community worldwide around women’s health while raising funds for breast cancer research. Next week, my team of trainers will be hosting virtual live classes over 24 hours to support this mission. 100% of every registration for Move to Cure classes will be donated to BCRF to help advance the world’s most promising research.

The 24-hour class schedule and registration is available now at tracyanderson.com/movetocure. Together we can help make the end of breast cancer a reality. 💓🎗💙

node.text: She came into the world a Cali girl who knows how to party and she is not one to ever disappoint.  My ride or die @koreyfitzhairz 🎉. I know what it feels like to spend a year away from you and may that NEVER happen again! I LOVE you! My hair has zero identity without you! Happy Birthday 👑♥️

node.text: And just like that, @candacebushnell came over for dinner... 💕 A performer has their dimensional moment, but it’s the creator who is the soul and heartbeat. It’s often times lonely being a creator given the study and careful crafting that is needed to advance into a dimension outside of your mind and off paper. Candace, you are a force and brilliant talent that forever changed and empowered how we women dance with NYC. I am honored to host you, and can’t wait to see your new show at the Bucks County Playhouse (I know that stage well 👯‍♀️)! Also can’t wait for you to write the next series that the world can fall in love and grow with! Bravo you brilliant being!!!

node.text: We all need help along our journey.  There isn’t a reality where challenges don’t exist and often times the scenes can change fast.  This weeks classes are about being present, being open, and doing the next right thing.  Focus on the here and now. What is currently challenging and what you might be doing to make it so difficult.  Learn to accept the difficulties and learn the skills to manage them.  How are you all managing this weeks @tracyandersononlinestudio content so far?? 💕

node.text: Be who you are, dress yourself in love, and join me tomorrow for a very special FundamenTAl Forward session at 9:30 AM EST in celebration of Pride Month. Some of you might remember the few surprise musical moments from last year, and I promise you this experience also won't disappoint. All class proceeds will be donated to the Hetrick-Martin Institute (@hetrickmartin) in support of LGBTQ+ youth, an organization I am so proud to be partnering with once again. Love you all 💕 Registration is now open at tracyanderson.com/live 🌈

node.text:
After 20 years of being in your homes, I am so excited to invite you inside mine. Thank you @ruemagazine for having me on your summer issue cover, but I think we all know who the real star is here 🐶 Find the new issue on newsstands on June 29th!

Photography by @davidengelhardt, story by @claire_the_celebrity_booker, glam by @koreyfitzhairz @elenamiglino, prop styling by @kevinhertzog, dog whispering by @stevenbeltrani. Thank you my brilliant friend @dannyseomag!
